reviews.text:
The restaurant was quiet, which was ok. But I fancy it is looking a bit tired from when it first opened. The food was good, although the deep fried ravioli which use to be large ravioli was just the regular sized squares making me think it was no longer made in the restaurant. The burger I had was excellent. 
The toilets were very shabby with the flush not working in the one I used. For a big name restaurant I think the standard have definitely slipped.

5-8pm $10-30 happy hours!!! You really can’t beat that!!!!!  We had a pleasant time with drinks and laugh. The food was also good; we had pizza and steak. Our 7-year-old kid also enjoyed eating there.
Convenient location and super good bargain for their happy hour drinks
Value for money, especially the happy hour. Just 10 to 30 per glass of wine, can't imagine. Location is good too, just behind times square
Vibrant contemporary place with a crazy happy hour arrangement. Go and explore yourself. Can't comment on the food since I don't eat European comfort food such as pizza etc.
